Summary of Qualifications

Proactive problem solving hands - on supervisor developer DBA and software architect.

Ability to effectively manage and complete multiple tasks and to shift priorities when required. Capable and willing to perform basic IT functions such as support hardware software configuration maintenance.

Proven ability to effectively train others clearly communicate and lead meetings. Capable of wearing a number of hats in a dynamic environment.

Experienced in managing and leading full life cycle development business/user requirements gathering technical specs/estimates designing coding testing integrating and deployment .

Detail-oriented quick learner with excellent verbal and written communication skills.

Effective at mediating across departments and divisions to accomplish successful outcomes.

Professional Experience confidential

Consultant - .Net Developer /SQL Server DBA-Developer

Software design/programming to support existing code base using C ASP.Net VB.Net Visual Studio 2012 with Team Foundation Server 2010 development and IIS web server including SharePoint administration.

Creating custom reports using SQL Server Reporting Services SSRS .

Construction of web services windows services using C to consolidate common code into easily accessible objects to be consumed by existing future applications.

Maintenance and development of web site Vendor as well as internal web site using VB.Net and ASP.Net Visual Studio 2012 .

Custom code maintenance and development to include 45 scheduled jobs inventory replenishment tools and other custom VB.Net VBA software which comprised roughly 130 separate Visual Studio solutions/projects.

Migrating existing VB.Net code base to C VS 2012 .

Monitoring server health capacity planning analyzing risk reporting potential problems.

Diagnosing critical failures in existing software infrastructure redesigning modules to decrease overall failure rate.

Constructing common software libraries/web services for use in applications.

confidential

Senior Interface Developer/Database Developer

Ongoing maintenance of HL7 health systems interfaces written in Visual Basic C to support the exchange of data between medical facilities/systems labs Lab Corp DR Systems Solstas/Spectrum McKesson Dell Physician Services Sectra and physician practices using NextGen EMR/EPM systems.

Developed windows services and WCF/SOAP web services to facilitate the exchange of data between disparate medical systems.

Resolved discrepancies between interface logic and vendor specific HL7 specs.

Design and development of database related objects stored procedures triggers tables etc. to abstract HL7 and vendor specific requirements.

Troubleshooting maintenance of file TCP based communications services used in exchanging HL7 messages.

Designed and developed large scale EMR/EHR integration routing engine solution to assist healthcare organizations with consolidating vendor specific HL7 2.x and CCD/CDA medical records formats Cerner Allscripts Greenway NetxGen etc for acute ambulatory facilities promoting better communication between hospitals practices laboratory facilities. The engine employs a number of technologies including SQL Server 2012 SSIS and ASP.Net with MVC Entity Framework windows services C WCF web services UltraPort HL7 Schema Engine developed within a hybrid Agile/Waterfall development environment using Team Foundation Server.

confidential

VB.Net Visual Studio 2010 with Team Foundation Server 2010 development and IIS web server including SharePoint administration.

Providing diagnostic tuning metrics in order to maximize uptime and throughput.

Implementing standardized solutions to improve the software design life-cycle to provide a conduit for improved communication enterprise wide change control source code control issue tracking asset management project management .

Gathering and analyzing requirements from department heads users stakeholders to enhance existing software and to build additional features modules for greater efficiency reliability and overall functionality.

Evaluating third party software investigating solutions to existing company needs.

Utilized Microsoft SQL Server 2000 ASP ADO Visual Basic Visual C COM components Windows Systems services daemons FrontPage and Adobe Acrobat SDK.

Designed a system which automated the completion of IRS 501c3 tax forms for nonprofits and churches. The completed solution took on the form of a web based interview that produced a completed 501c3 in PDF format similar to the TurboTax process.

SQL Server database performance tuning using Quest Spotlight Query Analyzer/Profiler.

Creation of SSIS integration services DTS packages for data migration and ETL of raw data from various sources flat files XML data ISAM data etc .

Areas of expertise include imaging systems document workflow database programming and web development.

Promoted to Principal Architect to manage lead 2 million internal reengineering project.

Implemented horizontal vertical partitioning of OLTP data through transactional replication for web farms.

Designed developed system add-ons to satisfy business requirements. Enhanced the OrderPoint site by designing interfaces to Carfax R.L. Polk KnowX Information America AutoTrack DBT and ChoicePoint s C.L.U.E/I2K system for VIN checks background checks criminal histories and vehicle claim history respectively.

Promoted to VP/Director of Information Systems after successfully managing the migration of systems applications to Windows NT SQL Server supervising and mentoring team of 7 full-time and 15 contract employees.

Introduced a computer based training program held on-site training seminars for both staff and contract developers.

Interfaced with project stakeholders to determine scope and objective.

Derived and created technical specifications and estimates from business requirements.

Routinely performed project management functions to steer projects towards successful outcomes.

Evaluated potential joint ventures/acquisitions and anticipated potential technical issues. Defined and enforced department/company policies guidelines practices and standards.

Served as technical liaison during the sale of RRS to ChoicePoint Confidential Insurance Services .

Assisted in the due diligence process during the acquisition of other public records firms such as L S Reporting ARS.

Senior Programmer/Analyst

Led the design of medical dental software used by franchised billing centers to transmit medical billing information to a number of national claims clearinghouses.

Developed DOS Windows based medical practice management billing software using Borland C/C .

Reviewed implemented electronic claims specs NSF ANSI HCFA 1500/UB92 from clearinghouses such as CyData/CyCare ETS NEIC Envoy and derived business requirements/technical specifications.

Developed the MedRemote/MedHost software which captured medical claim information from 3rd party practice management software and merged the captured information with our own products to eliminate double data entry at our satellite offices. Products developed were written using Borland C Sequiter Codebase Visual Basic an Empress RDBMS and dBase.

Developed telemarketing software that assisted with decreasing expenses by over 15 000 per month.

Supervised team of 5 full-time employees providing mentoring project prioritization resource management.

Reported directly to and collaborated with the President to develop projects in support of business initiatives.

Provided weekly updates in regards to project initiatives and system performance.

Developed DOS/UNIX applications procured and installed equipment in support of 132 station AT T UNIX system and performed routine UNIX system/network administration.

Staff scheduling and project tracking to ensure that deadlines are met. Management of network systems development and testing.
